    oc:appliesToContext "Between Step 3 data collection and Step 4 document generation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify all intermediate files are present and populated before generating the document. Print a verification summary. If any file is missing, warn but continue — the tear sheet handles missing data gracefully." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Ensures visibility into what data was lost before committing to document generation; prevents silent data gaps." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_57992170 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During Step 3b (Calculate Derived Metrics)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "During the calculation pass, enforce all arithmetic checks: margins match raw component ratios, growth rates compute correctly, segment totals sum to revenue, percentage columns sum to ~100%, and EV cross-checks hold. Flag failures as 'N/A' rather than publishing incorrect numbers." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Quiet math errors in a tear sheet destroy credibility; validation catches errors before they reach the document." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_5b54bdf4 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When considering adding management sections to any tear sheet type" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not include Management Team tables. No S&P Global tool returns executive data. Management names from training data will be stale." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Violates Data Integrity Rule 1 (no training data) and produces stale information." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_5ef9e131 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating tear sheets for private companies" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For private companies: skip stock price, 52-week range, beta, stock performance, consensus estimates, and trading comps. Lean into business overview, relationships, ownership structure, and whatever financials are available. Note 'Private Company' prominently in the header." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Private company data is sparser in CIQ; public-market-specific sections would be empty placeholders." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_67261353 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When populating any financial data point" ;
    oc:directiveContent "S&P Global tools are the only source for financial data. Never fill gaps with training knowledge — it may be stale or wrong. Label unknowns as 'N/A' or 'Not disclosed'." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Training data is temporally unreliable for financial figures; CIQ data is authoritative." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_71332e2b a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating more than one tear sheet type for the same company" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If generating multiple tear sheets for the same company in the same session, reuse the same retrieved data values. Net debt, revenue, EBITDA, margins, and growth rates must match exactly across all outputs." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Inconsistency across outputs for the same company undermines credibility." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_734ffcbc a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When both raw and pre-computed values are available" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Prefer MCP-returned fields over manual computation. Use pre-computed values (net debt, EBITDA, FCF) directly. Only compute derived metrics when tools don't return the field." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Reduces discrepancies between tool-sourced values and manually computed ones." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7edde29c a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When any data point is missing from MCP tool responses" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never fabricate data. If tools don't return a number, do not estimate from training knowledge. Use 'N/A' or 'Not disclosed'." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Fabricated financial data destroys tear sheet credibility and can lead to erroneous decisions." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_8e57935e a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building Valuation Snapshot or Trading Comps tables for ER, IB, and Corp Dev audiences" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always include forward (NTM) multiples when available from tools. Never show only trailing multiples when forward data exists." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Forward multiples are the primary valuation reference for professional audiences; trailing-only is a significant gap." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a97e4d56 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When starting any tear sheet generation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If the user doesn't specify an audience type, ask. The four types (Equity Research, IB/M&A, Corp Dev, Sales/BD) produce fundamentally different documents." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Audience determines sections, query plan, formatting density, and page length defaults." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_c4e0358f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When computing '% of Total' for segment tables" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use consolidated revenue as the denominator for segment percentages, not the sum of segment revenues. The sum of segments often exceeds consolidated revenue due to intersegment eliminations." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Ensures percentages align with the total revenue figure shown elsewhere in the document." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_ea0312e4 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When MCP tool responses are missing expected data" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If a tool call returns incomplete results, try alternative tools or narrower queries. If still incomplete after a targeted retry, label 'N/A' and move on." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Spending excessive retries on a single data point delays the entire tear sheet; graceful degradation maintains quality." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_f9f258f0 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When retrieving historical financials" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always pull 4 fiscal years of financial data even though only 3 are displayed. The fourth (earliest) year is needed to compute YoY revenue growth for the first displayed year." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without the fourth year, the earliest displayed year's growth rate shows 'N/A', which looks like missing data." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_ff139250 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During Step 3 data retrieval" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Write all intermediate data to files immediately after each MCP query. These files — not conversation context — are the single source of truth for every number in the document." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Data persisted to disk is protected from context degradation in long conversations; prevents numeric drift." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:req_2a4217a1 a oc:RequirementTool ;
    oc:isOptional false ;
    oc:requirementValue "docx-js (Node.js library)" .

oc:req_2b5e6ff0 a oc:RequirementKnowledge ;
    oc:isOptional false ;
    oc:requirementValue "Financial modeling and tear sheet conventions" .

oc:req_4a6cae28 a oc:RequirementAPI ;
    oc:isOptional false ;
    oc:requirementValue "S&P Global MCP tools (Kensho LLM-ready API)" .

_:ref_09a76eb945cfd1d4 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Call `createSectionHeader(...)` for every section title — never manually set paragraph borders" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_3" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

_:ref_0ad39398d4a32235 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Rewrite every narrative section for the audience.** The CIQ company summary is an input, not an output. Each audience type needs a different description: concise and thesis-oriented for equity research, pitchbook prose for IB, product-focused for Corp Dev, plain language for Sales/BD. Never paste the CIQ summary verbatim into any tear sheet." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_1" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

_:ref_0bae7273b5f12ff6 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Audience** — one of four types:" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:hasChild [ a oc:BulletList ;
            oc:blockType "bullet_list" ;
            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
            oc:hasItem [ a oc:BulletItem ;
                    oc:blockType "bullet_item" ;
                    oc:itemOrder 4 ;
                    oc:itemText "**Sales / BD** — for commercial teams preparing for a client meeting" ],
                [ a oc:BulletItem ;
                    oc:blockType "bullet_item" ;
                    oc:itemOrder 2 ;
                    oc:itemText "**IB / M&A** — for bankers profiling a company in transaction context" ],
                [ a oc:BulletItem ;
                    oc:blockType "bullet_item" ;
                    oc:itemOrder 1 ;
                    oc:itemText "**Equity Research** — for buy-side/sell-side analysts evaluating an investment" ],
                [ a oc:BulletItem ;
                    oc:blockType "bullet_item" ;
                    oc:itemOrder 3 ;
                    oc:itemText "**Corp Dev** — for internal strategic teams evaluating an acquisition target" ] ] ;
    oc:stepId "step_2" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

_:ref_228ecb8484be5e94 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Call `createTable(...)` for **all** tabular data — financial summaries, trading comps, M&A activity, relationship tables, funding history, etc. Pass `{ accentHeader: true }` for M&A activity tables (IB/M&A template). For non-numeric tables (e.g., relationships, ownership), the function still works correctly — it only right-aligns cells that contain numeric values." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_4" ;
    oc:stepOrder 4 .

_:ref_2c366759e513e9bf a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Differentiate earnings highlights by audience.** The same earnings call produces different takeaways for different readers. Equity research wants segment-level performance and consensus beat/miss. IB wants margin trajectory and strategic commentary. Sales/BD wants strategic themes that create conversation angles. Do not reuse the same bullets across tear sheet types." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_2" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

_:ref_3eb7e2802c01d394 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**S&P Global tools are the only source for financial data.** Do not fill gaps with training knowledge — it may be stale or wrong." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_1" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

_:ref_502717018549e706 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Prefer MCP-returned fields over manual computation.** If the S&P Global tools return a pre-computed field (e.g., net debt, EBITDA, FCF), use that value directly rather than computing it from components. Only compute derived metrics manually when the tools do not return the field. This reduces discrepancies." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_5" ;
    oc:stepOrder 5 .

_:ref_599825db1f7c4928 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Never downgrade known transaction values.** If the M&A tools return a deal value for a transaction, that value must appear in the output. Do not replace a known deal value with \"Undisclosed.\" Use \"Undisclosed\" only when the tools genuinely return no value for a transaction." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_7" ;
    oc:stepOrder 7 .

_:ref_600167e0f8ab1728 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Ensure consistency across tear sheet types.** If generating multiple tear sheets for the same company (e.g., equity research and IB/M&A in the same session), the same underlying data points must produce identical values across all outputs. Net debt, revenue, EBITDA, margins, and growth rates must match exactly. Do not re-query or re-compute independently per report — reuse the same retrieved values." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_6" ;
    oc:stepOrder 6 .

_:ref_6272c93d3b2edda4 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Synthesis sections are the differentiator.** Strategic Fit Analysis, Integration Considerations, Conversation Starters, and Business Overview paragraphs are where the tear sheet earns its value. These sections require analytical reasoning that connects data points into a narrative — listing company names without context is not synthesis." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_3" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

_:ref_70fa205d08d83744 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Label what you can't find.** Use \"N/A\" or \"Not disclosed\" rather than omitting a row silently." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_2" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

_:ref_761668cb786fc033 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Call `createBulletList(items, \"informational\")` for relationship entries" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_6" ;
    oc:stepOrder 6 .

_:ref_95b9238171d7d771 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Use consolidated revenue as the denominator for segment percentages.** When computing \"% of Total\" for segment tables, divide each segment's revenue by consolidated total revenue (as reported on the income statement), not by the sum of segment revenues. The sum of segments often exceeds consolidated revenue due to intersegment eliminations. Using consolidated revenue ensures percentages align with the total revenue figure shown elsewhere in the document." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_8" ;
    oc:stepOrder 8 .

_:ref_97427ccc999ff951 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Call `createBulletList(items, \"synthesis\")` for earnings highlights, strategic fit, integration considerations, and conversation starters" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_5" ;
    oc:stepOrder 5 .

_:ref_a35434cb736f4dff a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Company** — name or ticker. If only a ticker, resolve the full company name with an initial query (e.g., use the company info tool)." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_1" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

_:ref_a7e14fc0e211f115 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Copy all functions and constants above into the generated Node.js script" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_1" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

_:ref_b37fc3ac6ff82724 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Flag pending divestitures in segment tables.** If a company has announced a pending divestiture of a segment or business unit, add a footnote or parenthetical to the segment table noting the pending transaction (e.g., \"Mobility* — *Pending divestiture, expected mid-2026\"). For Corp Dev and IB/M&A tear sheets, include a one-line note below the segment table showing pro-forma revenue and revenue mix excluding the divested segment. This helps the reader evaluate the \"go-forward\" business without doing the math themselves." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_4" ;
    oc:stepOrder 4 .

_:ref_b9ed4b0daed24dd2 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Always include forward (NTM) multiples when available.** If the tools return both trailing and forward valuation multiples, both must appear in the output. Forward multiples are the primary valuation reference for equity research, IB/M&A, and corp dev audiences. Never show only trailing multiples when forward data is available." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_9" ;
    oc:stepOrder 9 .

_:ref_c4f10cc8eb3943b9 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**No S&P Global tool returns executive or management data.** Do not populate management names, titles, or biographical details from training data — this violates Rule 1 and produces stale information. If a management section appears in a template, omit it entirely. Ownership structure (institutional holders, insider %, PE sponsor) may be included only if returned by the tools — gate with \"data permitting.\"" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_10" ;
    oc:stepOrder 10 .

_:ref_cf1634880c9efac5 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Page length preference** (optional) — defaults vary by audience (see below), but the user can override." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_4" ;
    oc:stepOrder 4 .

_:ref_cf3c05d5dc4c98dc a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Pass `createFooter(date)` to the Document constructor's `footers.default` property" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_7" ;
    oc:stepOrder 7 .

_:ref_d6f4e954397a37c0 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Don't mix reporting periods.** If you have FY2023 revenue and LTM EBITDA, label them distinctly." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_4" ;
    oc:stepOrder 4 .

_:ref_f10cf5d84075b048 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Comparable companies** (optional) — if the user has specific comps in mind, note them. Otherwise the skill will identify peers from S&P Global data. This matters for Equity Research, IB/M&A, and Corp Dev tear sheets." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_3" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

_:ref_faae1ea8b8d918a9 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Call `createHeaderBanner(...)` instead of manually building banner paragraphs and tables" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_2" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

_:ref_fae1cbb9b15a2098 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Dates matter.** Note the fiscal year end or reporting period. Don't assume calendar year = fiscal year. Market data (stock prices, market cap) should include an \"as of\" date." ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_3" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

